GateDocument.TextWithNodes: - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - S B M I D I A ' 9 8 4 th Brazilian Symposium on Multimedia and Hypermedia Systems Rio de Janeiro - Brazil 29 - 31 May 1998 CALL FOR PAPERS The Brazilian Symposium on Multimedia and Hypermedia Systems ( SBMIDIA'98 ) , previously edited as Workshop on Multimedia and Hypermedia Systems , has now become an annual event sponsored by the Brazilian Computer Society ( SBC ) . SBMIDIA'98 is the main forum in South America for the dissemination of the latest results in theory , systems and applications of multimedia and hypermedia technology , as well as human-computer interaction . SBMIDIA'98 programme contains technical sessions , tutorials , short courses and panels , and also the exibition of software and equipments . CALL FOR CONTRIBUTIONS Authors are invited to submit papers reporting original , finished and ongoing research work related to all aspects of Multimedia and Hypermedia Systems . Accepted papers will appear in the Workshop Proceedings . Areas of interest include , but are not limited to , the following : . Multimedia / Hypermedia Applications . Tools and Environments for Multimedia / Hypermedia Systems . Modeling and Evaluation . Interoperability of Multimedia / Hypermedia Systems . Hyperdocument Engineering . World Wide Web . Syncronization of Multimedia / Hypermedia Objects . Quality of Service for Multimedia / Hypermedia Components . Management of Multimedia / Hypermedia Objects . Distributed Applications and CSCW . Integrated Workflow and Hyperdocuments . Formal Methods for Multimedia / Hypermedia Systems . Methods for the Design of the Human- Computer Interaction . Support for the Designer of HCI : Guidelines , Metrics and Prototyping . Evaluation of User- Computer Interaction SUBMISSION GUIDELINES Authors are invited to submit their contribution electronically ( in postscript ou MSWORD ) to the program commitee chair ( address below ) by the submission deadline . Please ensure that your email address is present , current and correct in all correspondence . Papers should be written in Portuguese or English . Papers should be formatted in A 4 paper ( 29 , 7 x 21 , 0 cm ) using 12 pt Times New Roman font , with an average of 40 to 45 lines per page , single column . Papers must have a maximum of 12 pages , including figures , tables , diagrams , references and appendices , all in black and write . The first page must include the title , authors' complete name , affiliation , postal and electronic address and a short abstract in English . The body of the paper should start soon after the abstract . Accepted papers will appear in the proceedings with a 70 % reduction . Therefore , we advise participants to avoid small details in figures and tables , since they may be missed .
